cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.MM 

The paper discusses an indexing architecture for storing and searching high-dimensional vectors, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The approach is based on statistical signal processing and decision theory, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper demonstrates the practical interest of the approach in a large-scale image search scenario, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
